es\", \"from\": 172, \"to\": 183}, {\"ngram\": \"societal norms\", \"from\": 188, \"to\": 202}, {\"ngram\": \"boxing\", \"from\": 234, \"to\": 240}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The young fighter from a quaint neighbourhood in Nizamabad in the southern state of Telangana dreamed of becoming the best female boxer in India, but little did she know she would exceed even that lofty aspiration.\", \"from\": 262, \"to\": 476, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 311, \"end\": 320, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nizamabad_district\", \"score\": 0.9999995866997723, \"rank\": 4.1330032074606463e-07, \"text\": \"Nizamabad\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nizamabad_district\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nizamabad_district\"}, {\"begin\": 346, \"end\": 355, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Telangana\", \"score\": 0.9999989645885665, \"rank\": 1.0354086457957813e-06, \"text\": \"Telangana\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Telangana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Telangana\"}, {\"begin\": 401, \"end\": 406, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"score\": 0.9998313323195767, \"rank\": 0.00016436956861338623, \"text\": \"India\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The young fighter\", \"from\": 262, \"to\": 279}, {\"ngram\": \"a quaint neighbourhood\", \"from\": 285, \"to\": 307}, {\"ngram\": \"the southern state\", \"from\": 324, \"to\": 342}, {\"ngram\": \"the best female boxer\", \"from\": 376, \"to\": 397}, {\"ngram\": \"even that lofty aspiration\", \"from\": 449, \"to\": 475}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Zareen's promising career began with a resounding victory at the Youth World Championships in 2011.\", \"from\": 478, \"to\": 577, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Zareen's promising career\", \"from\": 478, \"to\": 503}, {\"ngram\": \"a resounding victory\", \"from\": 515, \"to\": 535}, {\"ngram\": \"the Youth World Championships\", \"from\": 539, \"to\": 568}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And 11 years later, in 2022, she clinched gold in the 52kg category at the senior World Championships - a feat that positioned her alongside the legendary boxer Mary Kom, who won India's first-ever Olympic medal in women's boxing at the 2012 London Games.\", \"from\": 578, \"to\": 833, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 739, \"end\": 747, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mary_Kom\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.83147677582226e-65, \"text\": \"Mary Kom\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mary_Kom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mary_Kom\"}, {\"begin\": 757, \"end\": 762, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"score\": 0.9998313323195767, \"rank\": 0.00016436956861338623, \"text\": \"India\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 620, \"to\": 624}, {\"ngram\": \"the 52kg category\", \"from\": 628, \"to\": 645}, {\"ngram\": \"the senior World Championships\", \"from\": 649, \"to\": 679}, {\"ngram\": \"a feat\", \"from\": 682, \"to\": 688}, {\"ngram\": \"the legendary boxer\", \"from\": 719, \"to\": 738}, {\"ngram\": \"women's boxing\", \"from\": 793, \"to\": 807}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2012 London Games\", \"from\": 811, \"to\": 832}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a strategic move, Zareen transitioned to the 50kg category in 2023, aligning with the weight class featured in the Paris 2024 Olympic roster, and promptly secured her second IBA World Championship gold medal.\", \"from\": 835, \"to\": 1046, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 953, \"end\": 963, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.524553726063858e-17, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a strategic move\", \"from\": 838, \"to\": 854}, {\"ngram\": \"Zareen\", \"from\": 856, \"to\": 862}, {\"ngram\": \"the 50kg category\", \"from\": 879, \"to\": 896}, {\"ngram\": \"the weight class\", \"from\": 920, \"to\": 936}, {\"ngram\": \"her second IBA World Championship gold medal\", \"from\": 1001, \"to\": 1045}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Having consolidated her position as the boxer to beat in her division, Zareen has emerged as one of the strong medal chances at the Paris 2024 Olympics, which begin on July 26.\", \"from\": 1048, \"to\": 1224, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"her position\", \"from\": 1068, \"to\": 1080}, {\"ngram\": \"the boxer\", \"from\": 1084, \"to\": 1093}, {\"ngram\": \"her division\", \"from\": 1105, \"to\": 1117}, {\"ngram\": \"Zareen\", \"from\": 1119, \"to\": 1125}, {\"ngram\": \"the strong medal chances\", \"from\": 1148, \"to\": 1172}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris 2024 Olympics\", \"from\": 1176, \"to\": 1199}, {\"ngram\": \"July\", \"from\": 1216, \"to\": 1220}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Only two Indian female boxers have ever won an Olympic medal: Kom's 2012 bronze came in the Flyweight division and Lovlina Borgohain collected a bronze in the Welterweight division at Tokyo 2020.\", \"from\": 1226, \"to\": 1421, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1235, \"end\": 1241, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"score\": 0.7318875362166184, \"rank\": 0.3651854665146848, \"text\": \"Indian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\"}, {\"begin\": 1288, \"end\": 1291, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FK_Kom\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 7.461073846091754e-13, \"text\": \"Kom\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"htt